ErlaNGinE

The Erlang, Web and CouchDB experimental concept

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS

* Install git.

For Debian-based linux: apt-get install git-core
For others see http://github.com/guides/home

* Obtain sources:

git clone git://github.com/dmi/erlangine.git

* Compile

cd erlangine
make

* Install apache CouchDB 0.9.

Follow http://couchdb.apache.org/

Replace
  couchdb/share/couchdb/server/main.js
with
  erlangine/conf/main.js

If CouchDB's version has changed, You can use
  diff -R erlangine/conf/couch.js erlangine/conf/main.js
to obtain diff and patch couchdb script manually.

Run CouchDb on localhost

* Init

./start.sh maint
enge2:prepare_db().
entry:reset().
q().

* Run

./start.sh dev

* Try

- Point your browser to http://localhost:8080
- Register an account (Internet access to http://captchas.net required)
- Log in
- Create and save entries
- Search entries
- Edit and save entries

* Track ErlaNGinE blog

http://erlangine.feautec.pp.ru

* Enjoy
